President Barack Obama will award William Swenson, a former Army Captain, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Kunar Province, Afghanistan on September 8, 2009. Swenson will be the sixth living recipient to be awarded the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He will be honored for his selfless service as an Embedded Trainer and Mentor of the Afghan National Security Forces. Swenson's military background includes completing Officer Candidate School and various training courses. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate gallantry above and beyond the call of duty, involving great personal bravery or self-sacrifice.